WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:02.560
Well, good evening, family.

00:00:02.560 --> 00:00:05.546
Thank you for joining us again tonight.

00:00:05.546 --> 00:00:07.420
We're excited to pray with y'all.

00:00:07.420 --> 00:00:09.970
We have some things I want to share with you.

00:00:09.970 --> 00:00:11.474
First, all glory to Jesus.

00:00:11.474 --> 00:00:13.640
We have no incidents today at all.

00:00:13.640 --> 00:00:17.040
And I just want to give God praise right now.

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:22.559
I believe it's the fervent prayers of the righteous that avail much.

00:00:22.999 --> 00:00:34.399
It's because of you and me, and other prayer groups around the United States, that we're praying and changing things through the power of prayer and the authority of the believer.

00:00:34.729 --> 00:00:38.297
We're able to pray for the shopping, that there were no casualties.

00:00:38.297 --> 00:00:39.920
We only had one major incident.

00:00:39.920 --> 00:00:51.413
We pray for the family that lost their daughter in the tragic, terrible incident in Washington the day before Thanksgiving.

00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:53.440
That was awful.

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:55.920
And she went home; I pray she knew Jesus Christ.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:01:01.303
That's why I try to tell you all the time, none of us are promised tomorrow.

00:01:01.303 --> 00:01:09.223
I'm sure she didn't know that day that she would pass away and that the tragic thing was going to happen.

00:01:09.223 --> 00:01:12.120
You never want to take this time for granted.

00:01:12.400 --> 00:01:14.620
Always look at the now.

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:19.360
Thank God that we have now and give your heart to Jesus Christ.

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:21.600
You must know Him.

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:24.750
You must know that tomorrow's not promised.

00:01:25.180 --> 00:01:29.887
We pray for her family and for the loss.

00:01:29.887 --> 00:01:34.090
I don't know if she had children or what, but that was a very sad situation.

00:01:34.090 --> 00:01:41.280
I don't know if the other man passed away, but thank God it was not more.

00:01:41.280 --> 00:01:44.299
Thank God that today we didn't see anything.

00:01:44.299 --> 00:01:52.192
I still have an urgency to pray over the shopping all through this season.

00:01:52.192 --> 00:02:02.331
Continually praying over the economy, our nation, the nation's capital, and the White House tree ceremony with the lighting of the tree.

00:02:05.782 --> 00:02:22.506
Praying over the Rockefeller Times Square tree ceremony—that's why that's behind us tonight—and continually lifting up New Year's Eve and all the holiday season, that no weapon formed against this nation shall prosper.

00:02:23.179 --> 00:02:29.120
You always get the critics who say, 'Well, Brandon, don't you think we should have heard something?

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:31.864
' No, 'no news is good news' in my opinion.

00:02:31.864 --> 00:02:33.519
I don't care if we ever hear.

00:02:33.519 --> 00:02:34.587
I'm still going to stand on the wall.

00:02:34.587 --> 00:02:35.280
I'm going to still yell.

00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:45.840
I'm going to tell you what's coming, what I see, and what the Lord keeps revealing to me: to pray for our nation and keep doing my job.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:59.119
I believe if we do see major things like we saw in Washington DC, where one person passed away—I don't know if the other one's still alive—but that's a prayer fail.

00:02:59.119 --> 00:03:01.309
We don't want anything to happen.

00:03:03.309 --> 00:03:07.360
I warned you the people have infiltrated this nation.

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:16.459
And this guy, for all the things being said that he worked for the CIA and that the Trump administration pardoned him, I'm still looking into that.

00:03:19.142 --> 00:03:22.264
You don't know what's fake news and what's real news.

00:03:22.264 --> 00:03:24.288
So, I just try not to get into the conspiracies.

00:03:28.656 --> 00:03:36.263
I want to start off with this, and this is my opinion.

00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:40.759
Everything that I say about this is my opinion, and it's not me telling you to do anything.

00:03:40.759 --> 00:03:46.480
I want you to pray about everything I bring to you tonight and take it to God in prayer.

00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:53.731
It's not an act of fear or worry; it's just what my wife and I do.

00:03:55.733 --> 00:03:58.631
We believe this, but I do not bring it up very often.

00:03:58.862 --> 00:04:06.551
I talked to my mom on the phone today, and she was talking about some of the things she and my extended family do.

00:04:09.030 --> 00:04:17.816
I thought, 'Well, I don't like talking about this stuff because a lot of people do not agree with it, especially in the circles that we're in.

00:04:17.816 --> 00:04:22.503
' But I'm going to talk about it.

00:04:22.503 --> 00:04:25.610
I think it's wisdom sometimes just to present it.

00:04:25.610 --> 00:04:30.596
You do what you want with it, but that's what Diana and I do.

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:34.620
You're like, 'What is it, Brandon?

00:04:34.620 --> 00:04:37.456
Oh my god, it's a conspiracy.

00:04:37.456 --> 00:04:38.080
' No.

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:50.320
I want to talk to you about wheat and making homemade breads—shelf life for what I believe is coming.

00:04:50.320 --> 00:04:54.187
You don't have to do this, but this is what Diana and I do.

00:04:54.187 --> 00:04:59.509
We believe in making this wheat.

00:04:59.509 --> 00:05:07.199
It's just grains, but we've bought a mill and we make homemade breads.

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:09.520
They're wheat berries.

00:05:11.969 --> 00:05:21.440
We send them through the mill and we make the bread because all the bread we get at the store has lost all its nutrients.

00:05:21.440 --> 00:05:22.171
It's trash.

00:05:22.171 --> 00:05:24.620
I'm just telling y'all, they bleach it.

00:05:24.620 --> 00:05:31.000
They do all kinds of terrible things to our breads; there are pesticides.

00:05:36.080 --> 00:05:36.399
We get this—it's organic.

00:05:38.150 --> 00:05:38.372
This is amazing stuff.

00:05:38.372 --> 00:05:50.986
If you have constipation issues, we have found that if you eat this on a regular basis, it really rubs the walls of your colon and causes you to have bowel movements.

00:05:55.220 --> 00:06:05.053
My daughter takes this wheat and she mills things for me: fresh muffins, fresh tortillas.

00:06:07.469 --> 00:06:10.960
This has shelf life for the end times.

00:06:11.260 --> 00:06:13.060
You don't ever have to worry.

00:06:14.240 --> 00:06:18.036
We had friends talk to us about it.

00:06:20.496 --> 00:06:28.533
I was asking God for an alternative to that survival food a big ministry in Branson sells.

00:06:33.330 --> 00:06:47.840
I was looking at the content inside these buckets, this 30-year shelf-life food, and in the natural, folks, you maybe could eat it for a couple of weeks, but it's not good for you.

00:06:48.498 --> 00:06:49.813
This stuff is bad.

00:06:50.142 --> 00:07:05.520
I know what the Father has told me is coming, and I know He's extended time and is doing things right by letting us pray for revival, but we all know the end times are coming.

00:07:12.100 --> 00:07:15.177
People always ask me, 'Brandon, do you believe in storing food back?

00:07:15.177 --> 00:07:20.857
' I don't like, like I said, the 30-year shelf-life food.

00:07:20.857 --> 00:07:21.783
It's not healthy.

00:07:21.783 --> 00:07:28.512
But wheat lasts if you have these tubs and tighten the lid to keep the oxygen off of it.

00:07:34.186 --> 00:07:35.519
You can grind up the wheat and make fresh breads to take care of your family.

00:07:36.319 --> 00:07:42.115
You can find YouTube videos if you search 'freshly milled flour' or 'freshly milled bread.

00:07:42.115 --> 00:07:47.060
' It talks about wheat berries, and a lot of people are doing it.

00:07:58.079 --> 00:08:02.960
So, there are a lot of instructional videos of how to do it.

00:08:06.352 --> 00:08:15.280
I try to think of how you stay alive and take care of yourself if things were to happen and the grid was to go down.

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:25.599
Even for people who want to criticize, ', you said this, said that,' even FEMA and our government tell you to have at least a week's worth of food.

00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.417
That's not stupid; that's just being prepared.

00:08:31.417 --> 00:08:33.160
People get all bent out of shape.

00:08:33.160 --> 00:08:34.422
'Well, are you living in fear?

00:08:34.422 --> 00:08:36.583
You're not quoting the word.

00:08:36.583 --> 00:08:39.920
' No, I didn't say be stupid.

00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:46.880
I said have enough that your family can be taken care of in case of an emergency.

00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:51.680
Most people travel with a spare tire and jumper cables.

00:08:52.030 --> 00:08:54.480
Are you expecting to have a flat?

00:08:54.903 --> 00:08:56.594
But you have it.

00:08:56.594 --> 00:08:59.860
I'm not anticipating a flat, but you have the spare tire.

00:09:01.509 --> 00:09:05.920
I don't anticipate having one, but it's there for an emergency.

00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:12.720
I don't anticipate having a dead battery, but you have jumper cables because of the emergency or roadside assistance.

00:09:14.760 --> 00:09:17.519
For our insurance company, we buy extra for five bucks a month for AAA.

00:09:20.914 --> 00:09:23.943
Whenever you call them, they come.

00:09:25.200 --> 00:09:29.520
I pay for the insurance just in case.

00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:33.020
Life insurance is there just in case, if you can afford it.

00:09:33.020 --> 00:09:38.186
I don't anticipate dying, but if something were to happen, you want to make sure your family's taken care of.

00:09:38.186 --> 00:09:39.222
Life insurance is there.

00:09:40.571 --> 00:09:47.040
Sometimes you get really persecuted in the Word of Faith charismatic circle for saying some of the stuff I'm telling you, but I'm trying to warn you.

00:09:50.809 --> 00:09:53.360
I have seen a storm.

00:09:55.333 --> 00:10:05.244
We know that God is merciful and He'll take care of us, and we don't get in fear.

00:10:05.502 --> 00:10:17.360
The Lord showed us that we would pray over our pots of food and that there would be stuff appearing and that there'll be supernatural provision when there is no provision.

00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:24.784
But I believe you put your hand to the plow and you work, and God will bless your efforts.

00:10:24.784 --> 00:10:30.160
Joseph stored food for the famine.

00:10:30.160 --> 00:10:32.987
There were seven years of plenty and seven years not.

00:10:34.231 --> 00:10:36.520
He could have said, 'I don't really believe that.

00:10:36.520 --> 00:10:37.750
' What would have happened?

00:10:37.750 --> 00:10:41.031
So you just have to do what God tells you to do.

00:10:41.253 --> 00:10:46.090
This is just one instance people ask me about all the time because we eat it anyway.

00:10:46.090 --> 00:10:49.040
We love these muffins.

00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:53.954
It's not going to expire because we'll eat it before it does.

00:10:54.731 --> 00:11:00.196
She makes homemade cakes with this; she makes pie crust pastry.

00:11:00.196 --> 00:11:04.480
We make pie crusts and cakes and all kinds of things for birthdays.

00:11:05.630 --> 00:11:11.519
This is so much healthier than eating a sack of flour from Walmart.

00:11:11.519 --> 00:11:13.053
There are good nutrients in this.

00:11:13.053 --> 00:11:21.600
There are a lot of vitamins and minerals that they take out of your stuff because they mill it in the factory and bleach the flour.

00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:32.000
Number two, I was praying and I said, 'Lord, I don't like all of the vegetables and stuff from the store.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:34.079
I like organic.

00:11:34.079 --> 00:11:38.550
Teach me because it doesn't have a long shelf life.

00:11:38.550 --> 00:11:40.080
' If you learn how to can...

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:41.760
I had a lady named Sherry.

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:43.416
She was into canning food.

00:11:43.416 --> 00:11:50.491
She learned how to can pot roast meals and stored her house full of that, which was pretty brilliant because she eats that.

00:11:53.973 --> 00:11:58.460
She's a friend of ours from the old church.

00:11:59.040 --> 00:12:07.440
You get ideas that God will give you to sustain things, and you can eat it and rotate it out so you always have extra.

00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:14.240
Then there are Tower Gardens.

00:12:15.547 --> 00:12:18.693
Now, Tower Gardens are very wise.

00:12:20.293 --> 00:12:29.822
We have two of them, and you can grow your vegetables from these Tower Gardens that have lights on them.

00:12:30.071 --> 00:12:36.697
You can have a backup in case the grid goes down that runs off solar power.

00:12:36.697 --> 00:12:43.269
Solar power runs outside your house a little bit during the day so these lights shine during the winter.

00:12:43.760 --> 00:12:48.595
They have little seed pods, and you can grow tomatoes, cucumbers, lettuce, cabbage, carrots, whatever.

00:12:59.547 --> 00:13:11.500
It grows out of this and has a base where the water is always filtering up through it and feeds the plants what they need to sustain life.

00:13:11.800 --> 00:13:20.959
If you do it right, it'll produce five pounds of food a week per garden.

00:13:21.217 --> 00:13:23.609
You go by how much your family may need.

00:13:40.160 --> 00:13:40.606
Some say, 'Our family would eat 20 pounds of vegetables a week,' which is a lot.

00:13:40.606 --> 00:13:42.388
Ten for us.

00:13:42.388 --> 00:13:45.280
That's if you're just eating a vegan diet.

00:13:45.280 --> 00:13:53.760
You can eat a lot of vegan with some bread and good grains and sustain your life.

00:14:06.133 --> 00:14:06.427
We're not vegan, but meat takes cold to stay fresh.

00:14:06.427 --> 00:14:09.1000
It's hard to keep meat fresh if the grid's down.

00:14:14.950 --> 00:14:23.297
I have seen things about cyberattacks and electricity attacks where people are without this stuff for three and four weeks at a time.

00:14:23.297 --> 00:14:29.991
We're praying against it, but if it were to happen, how could you sustain your hamburger?

00:14:29.991 --> 00:14:32.639
How would you keep your freezer going?

00:14:35.324 --> 00:14:35.493
I have a generator.

00:14:35.493 --> 00:14:41.257
How long can you keep a generator going with gas or natural gas for a long period?

00:14:52.800 --> 00:14:52.968
You could run it every three hours, but what if it's longer?

00:14:55.600 --> 00:15:03.332
I don't like to get into this because it becomes controversial for a lot of people, but I felt in my heart to do it tonight, and you can take it for what you want.

00:15:03.332 --> 00:15:06.008
Having a Tower Garden running off solar and a battery generator...

00:15:06.008 --> 00:15:08.080
it's a little thing; it's a Jackery.

00:15:08.080 --> 00:15:12.701
They have all different kinds of brands, but it's one of those little ones.

00:15:17.519 --> 00:15:17.901
I think we do have a Jackery.

00:15:17.901 --> 00:15:24.600
It lasts hours, and you can run a microwave on it for four or five hours.

00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:32.336
I think we paid like 800 bucks for it, and you can run your Tower Garden off of it and keep your plants alive.

00:15:32.336 --> 00:15:42.280
I'm not telling you what you should do; I'm trying to tell you what we do because we eat it anyway.

00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:44.137
It's not fear.

00:15:44.137 --> 00:15:47.900
It's good to eat vegetables and fresh bread.

00:15:48.560 --> 00:15:49.152
This is sustainable.

00:15:49.152 --> 00:15:58.559
You can buy tubs of it, rotate it out, and I don't know how many loaves of bread you can make with this and muffins.

00:16:08.500 --> 00:16:10.933
This turns into a lot.

00:16:12.720 --> 00:16:16.707
It expands when you mill it.

00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:20.000
It's fluffier.

00:16:21.759 --> 00:16:24.551
It looks like very little, but when you grind it up, it turns into a lot.

00:16:25.040 --> 00:16:31.493
If that was already milled, it would be a lot bigger.

00:16:31.902 --> 00:16:33.680
This right here is for backup, for power.

00:16:38.250 --> 00:16:39.279
We're not selling the brand.

00:16:40.937 --> 00:16:44.347
I'm not trying to sponsor it; I'm just trying to tell you.

00:16:44.347 --> 00:16:51.778
There are a lot of different brands that are amazing, but this is the one we got, and we plug our stuff into it.

00:16:53.421 --> 00:16:59.075
We got it on sale off Amazon, maybe Black Friday, so they might have good deals going on right now.

00:16:59.857 --> 00:17:01.739
We got solar panels and it charges it.

00:17:08.924 --> 00:17:12.440
In case of emergency, you put the solar panel out and it keeps stuff going.

00:17:12.840 --> 00:17:16.667
I'm just trying to give alternative ideas for you.

00:17:16.667 --> 00:17:20.880
I don't like the 30-year shelf life food.

00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:23.600
I don't think it's healthy for the body of Christ.

00:17:24.578 --> 00:17:27.199
If you believe in it and you sell it, that's on you.

00:17:27.199 --> 00:17:37.039
I'm just trying to say: what are alternative ideas that could help you, things you're already consuming that aren't way out there?

00:17:37.039 --> 00:17:39.380
The next thing would be chickens.

00:17:39.380 --> 00:17:46.160
Now, I know Sister Billie and her ministry; they have 30 chickens or more.

00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:47.670
I mean, they have a lot of chickens.

00:17:48.450 --> 00:17:54.756
Her son Terry and the rest of them have chickens; they lay eggs out there, and they fish and hunt.

00:17:56.133 --> 00:18:05.168
But we live in the city, so you can't kill deer, hunt, and fish because we don't have a place to go.

00:18:05.631 --> 00:18:07.448
So, you have to think outside the box.

00:18:07.448 --> 00:18:18.000
If you live in a major city like Chicago or New York, what could you do in case of an emergency?

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:22.799
I bring all this up for a reason, but I just don't get into it.

00:18:22.799 --> 00:18:26.640
There's much you do not know that I do not say, but that I pray over.

00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:32.747
I'm telling you now, there was a group of us in 2015 in our old church.

00:18:33.191 --> 00:18:39.120
We got all into survivalism, and people got into saving things back.

00:18:40.319 --> 00:18:42.280
People get real flaky with it.

00:18:44.018 --> 00:18:47.600
I never try to give advice, but I see these things and we pray over them.

00:18:48.100 --> 00:18:52.213
I had one YouTuber say, 'You're saying that you cost people their houses and everything.

00:18:52.213 --> 00:18:59.020
' No, they sold their houses to downsize because they thought the economy was going to crash.

00:18:59.020 --> 00:19:02.971
I didn't cause anybody to lose their house; it wasn't because of anything I said.

00:19:02.971 --> 00:19:09.040
They were already preppers and were downsizing their homes.

00:19:09.040 --> 00:19:11.006
Now, people try to say, 'Well, Brandon, you cost them their house.

00:19:11.006 --> 00:19:13.473
' I saw YouTube videos and I said, 'Are you kidding?

00:19:13.473 --> 00:19:14.856
I never cost anybody their house.

00:19:14.856 --> 00:19:19.280
' They sold their houses because of things that we were talking about and praying over.

00:19:20.080 --> 00:19:22.708
We were all in a prayer group; it's a church thing.

00:19:22.708 --> 00:19:23.760
It isn't on me.

00:19:25.383 --> 00:19:25.669
Adults are adults.

00:19:26.240 --> 00:19:31.230
If you're an adult, you put your big boy or big girl pants on; I'm not responsible for your household.

00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:32.460
But we pray.

00:19:32.460 --> 00:19:35.230
Now, if you're not a part of it, you automatically want to see...

00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:40.366
like the other pastors, they don't like some of the stuff you're saying because they're seeker-friendly.

00:19:40.366 --> 00:19:44.960
99% of the seeker-friendlies don't want to talk about this stuff, and they go, 'Well, you're causing fear.

00:19:44.960 --> 00:19:46.133
' So, shut up.

00:19:46.133 --> 00:19:48.640
We don't want you talking in our church anymore.

00:19:48.640 --> 00:19:49.300
That's fine.

00:19:49.300 --> 00:19:53.919
I have an opinion and I'm entitled to it, but I'm not telling you to do anything.

00:19:53.919 --> 00:19:56.880
This is what we do, and people have asked.

00:19:58.114 --> 00:20:01.520
The other part was coins.

00:20:01.520 --> 00:20:08.240
I like old silver coins that are tradable.

00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:12.490
Having things like this—this is a silver coin, an old coin from 1812.

00:20:22.640 --> 00:20:25.039
Old coins like that are junk silver.

00:20:28.947 --> 00:20:31.269
I always try to think outside the box regarding bartering.

00:20:31.269 --> 00:20:39.579
Well, if you have a chicken and I have a piece of silver, could I take this and barter with you to get a chicken?

00:20:39.579 --> 00:20:40.940
Because I like chicken.

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:44.480
And you can make a pot of noodles with this wheat.

00:20:44.480 --> 00:20:49.440
You make noodles out of it, boil a chicken, and you have chicken noodle soup.

00:20:49.440 --> 00:20:50.743
It's all part of it.

00:20:54.000 --> 00:21:05.280
And if you have change—I've found a lot of spare change in the past that would have old coins, like quarters from 1964 and older.

00:21:05.280 --> 00:21:17.760
If you go on YouTube and search it, you'll see they're worth more than a quarter; they're worth a few dollars because they're still 90% silver.

00:21:18.320 --> 00:21:22.274
So, having junk silver for bartering and trading is good.

00:21:24.306 --> 00:21:26.240
The other part is firearms.

00:21:26.240 --> 00:21:36.685
I know it's controversial and people get upset with me, but I am a man who believes in the Second Amendment.

00:21:36.685 --> 00:21:43.490
I believe that we have the right to bear arms and the right to defend your family.

00:21:43.490 --> 00:21:46.533
I do not back away from it or shy away from it.

00:21:46.533 --> 00:21:55.669
I know there's a lot of Christians that get really upset at me about that, but my wife and I are very trained in protecting ourselves with our firearms.

00:21:55.669 --> 00:22:01.890
You come through my front door uninvited and you kick it in, you won't be here the next day.

00:22:01.890 --> 00:22:04.280
I'm just telling you where we are.

00:22:04.280 --> 00:22:07.780
Now, people don't like that, but that's the honest-to-God truth.

00:22:07.780 --> 00:22:10.133
You kick in my door, you're not going to be here.

